<p>State officials urged Californians to turn off unnecessary appliances and lights to help avoid blackouts from an overwhelmed power grid.</p>

<p>Authorities also asked power generators to delay any maintenance until after the weekend to prevent blackouts like the two nights of rolling outages in mid-August as residents cranked up their air conditioning.</p>

<p>California has seen 900 wildfires since August 15, many of them started by an intense series of thousands of lightening strikes. The blazes have burned more than 1.5 million acres (2,343 square miles). There have been eight fire deaths and nearly 3,300 structures destroyed.              </p>
